                           District 1:  John D. Bruhn
                                                   [green_white_right.gif]

        Commissioner Bruhn is a lifelong resident of St. Lucie County,
   Florida. Born on 06/13/61 to Tommy & Carol Bruhn, Commissioner Bruhn
   was raised along with his two brothers Tommy,Jr. and Scotty in a
   loving, stable, and supportive family.

         During his high school years at Westwood High, Commissioner Bruhn
   participated in a variety of sports including football, golf, and
   tennis. Receiving a partial football scholarship upon graduation in
   1980, Commissioner Bruhn went on to attend Indian River Community
   College and the University of Central Florida. He obtained his law
   degree from St. Thomas School of Law in 1988. During his years as a
   student at St. Thomas School of Law, Commissioner Bruhn was a member of
   the Phi Alpha Delta fraternity and had begun to show an interest in
   politics. He was socially active and a member or president of several
   committees including the yearbook committee and the schools law
   newspaper.

         In 1988 Commissioner Bruhn returned to Ft. Pierce and opened his
   law office. He is also president of Legal Care Insurance and Adjunct
   Professor-IRCC. Commissioner Bruhn has been married to the former Miss
   Marla Mchaffey since 1988 and they have four children: Matthew, Steven,
   Michael, and Morgan.

         Commissioner Bruhn strongly feels that the children of St. Lucie
   County need recreational activities and facilities. He has sponsored
   and coached several youth organizations including T-Ball and soccer.
   When he can find the time, his own hobbies include bowling, fishing,
   and golf.

         Although Commissioner Bruhn has only held office since Nov.,
   1996, he sees a bright future ahead for St. Lucie County and hopes to
   make a positive difference for its citizens.
   [comm_bruhn.jpg]

